title: Catacombs
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Underground burial chambers used by early [[Christians|Christianity]] (and sometimes Jews) from the 2nd to 5th centuries CE. They were dug beneath cities like Rome and included tunnels, tombs, and small chapels decorated with [[frescoes|Fresco]] showing biblical scenes and symbols of faith.

''Example:'' The Catacombs of Priscilla in Rome, known for early [[Christian|Christianity]] wall paintings like “The Good Shepherd.”